OL,6,FHe said Labour would engage with the
OL,7,FBudget but added that his party was
OL,8,F"not in a strong negotiating position"
OL,9,Fbefore suggesting the Greens and Lib
OL,10,FDems were more likely to get a Budget
OL,11,Fdeal with First Minister John Swinney.
OL,13,FThe Budget will be Ms Robison's last
OL,14,Fbefore she stands down as an MSP at
OL,15,Fthe May election. Recent polling
OL,16,Fsuggests the SNP is in first place,
OL,17,Falthough not enough for a Holyrood
OL,18,Fmajority, with Reform and Labour in
OL,19,Fsecond and third place respectively.
